Our Story: The Heart Behind Wellderly 
Wellderly was co-founded by Amy and Klay Huddleston.
Amy is an Amazon trailblazer who owned and operated a multi-unit Home Instead senior care franchise enterprise for 25 years. A nationally recognized senior care expert and podcaster, her empathetic guidance has been sought by media, families, and caregivers for decades. After a successful sale to private equity, the requests for her wisdom never stopped — inspiring the bold question: How do we scale Amy’s 25+ years of real-world senior care expertise to guide family caregivers nationwide?
Klay Huddleston brings world-class technology and scaling expertise to the mission. He joined Amazon as employee #500 in 1998 and built a distinguished career in global marketing and digital transformation, eventually rising to Global Chief Marketing & Digital Officer roles. He later partnered with Amy on their Home Instead endeavors, negotiating a 5x EBITDA private equity exit. MIT xPRO-certified in AI Strategy and Leadership and a Certified Master Health and Wellness Coach, Klay is passionate about using AI-enhanced platforms to solve meaningful human challenges.
Together, Amy’s unmatched hands-on senior care wisdom and Klay’s proven ability to scale intelligent, user-centered solutions created Wellderly — an unbiased, AI-powered system that gives sandwich-generation families clarity, confidence, and time back.

